data.enText: the priests or ministers of a religion, especially of the Christian Church

data.chText: 所有当地的圣职人员都获邀参加这项仪式。
data.enText: All the local clergy were asked to attend the ceremony.

data.chText: 新的提案使神职人员和平信徒都会受到影响。
data.enText: The new proposals affect both clergy and laity.

tr: in Christianity, clergymen collectively (as distinguished from the laity)

value.def: The clergy are the official leaders of the religious activities of a particular group of believers.

example.ex: These proposals met opposition from the clergy.
example.tran: 这些提案遭到神职人员的反对。
